{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017bgrWZXudT5RyeVbZm3geb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Report: HealthDeps TypeCheck Error Analysis\n\n### What HealthDeps Expects\n\nThe `HealthDeps` interface is defined in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/health.ts` (lines 15-22) and expects:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface HealthDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  sql: postgres.Sql;           // ← Required property (the error)\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKey: PublicKey;\n  isWorkerRunning: () => boolean;\n  minSolBalance: number;\n}\n```\n\n### What the Test Is Passing\n\nIn the test file `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` at line 161-167, the test passes:\n\n```typescript\ncreateHealthRoutes({\n  db,\n  connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n  serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  isWorkerRunning: () => true,\n  minSolBalance: 0.1,\n});\n```\n\nThe test is **missing the `sql` property**, which causes a TypeScript compilation error.\n\n### Whether This Error Was Introduced by Spec 300 Changes\n\n**YES** — This was introduced by spec 300 referral system changes. The `sql` property was added to `HealthDeps` to support the new `getQueueDepth(sql)` call in health.ts (lines 78-79):\n\n```typescript\nif (verbose) {\n  try {\n    response.eventQueue = await getQueueDepth(sql);  // ← Uses sql parameter\n  } catch {\n    response.eventQueue = { pending: 0, processing: 0, dead: 0, completed: 0 };\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `getQueueDepth` function (in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/health.ts`) requires a `postgres.Sql` instance to query the `event_queue` table, which is part of the referral system's async event processing infrastructure introduced in spec 300.\n\nIn the production code (`index.ts` lines 221-231), the `sql` instance is correctly provided:\n\n```typescript\napp.route(\n  \"/health\",\n  createHealthRoutes({\n    db,\n    sql,                  // ← Correctly passed\n    connection,\n    serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n    isWorkerRunning: () => worker.isRunning,\n    minSolBalance: config.minSolBalance,\n  }),\n);\n```\n\n### The Minimal Fix Needed\n\nThe test needs to pass the `sql` instance to `createHealthRoutes`. In the test setup, you need to:\n\n1. The test file already has `rawSql` variable (line 98), which is the postgres instance\n2. Pass this `rawSql` as the `sql` parameter to `createHealthRoutes`:\n\n```typescript\ncreateHealthRoutes({\n  db,\n  sql: rawSql,  // ← Add this line\n  connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n  serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  isWorkerRunning: () => true,\n  minSolBalance: 0.1,\n});\n```\n\n**Root cause**: The spec 300 referral system added event queue monitoring to the health endpoint, which requires a direct SQL connection. The test was not updated to pass this new required parameter."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aebd834e80ef042f1 (use SendMessage with to: 'aebd834e80ef042f1' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 49992\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 65888</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e377e535-4c51-477c-a8e7-f05957c224f0","uuid":"8c92fdf3-2cf2-4a76-acc8-442b818271fb","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:21:39.844Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Check the following files to understand the HealthDeps typecheck error in the backend:\n\n1. Read `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` around line 161 to see the HealthDeps usage\n2. Find where HealthDeps is defined (grep for \"HealthDeps\" in the backend source)\n3. Determine what property `sql` is expected and whether this was introduced by spec 300 referral system changes or is pre-existing\n\nReport:\n- What HealthDeps expects\n- What the test is passing\n- Whether this error was introduced by spec 300 changes (check git blame/log if needed)\n- The minimal fix needed","agentId":"aebd834e80ef042f1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Report: HealthDeps TypeCheck Error Analysis\n\n### What HealthDeps Expects\n\nThe `HealthDeps` interface is defined in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/health.ts` (lines 15-22) and expects:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface HealthDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  sql: postgres.Sql;           // ← Required property (the error)\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKey: PublicKey;\n  isWorkerRunning: () => boolean;\n  minSolBalance: number;\n}\n```\n\n### What the Test Is Passing\n\nIn the test file `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` at line 161-167, the test passes:\n\n```typescript\ncreateHealthRoutes({\n  db,\n  connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n  serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  isWorkerRunning: () => true,\n  minSolBalance: 0.1,\n});\n```\n\nThe test is **missing the `sql` property**, which causes a TypeScript compilation error.\n\n### Whether This Error Was Introduced by Spec 300 Changes\n\n**YES** — This was introduced by spec 300 referral system changes. The `sql` property was added to `HealthDeps` to support the new `getQueueDepth(sql)` call in health.ts (lines 78-79):\n\n```typescript\nif (verbose) {\n  try {\n    response.eventQueue = await getQueueDepth(sql);  // ← Uses sql parameter\n  } catch {\n    response.eventQueue = { pending: 0, processing: 0, dead: 0, completed: 0 };\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `getQueueDepth` function (in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/health.ts`) requires a `postgres.Sql` instance to query the `event_queue` table, which is part of the referral system's async event processing infrastructure introduced in spec 300.\n\nIn the production code (`index.ts` lines 221-231), the `sql` instance is correctly provided:\n\n```typescript\napp.route(\n  \"/health\",\n  createHealthRoutes({\n    db,\n    sql,                  // ← Correctly passed\n    connection,\n    serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n    isWorkerRunning: () => worker.isRunning,\n    minSolBalance: config.minSolBalance,\n  }),\n);\n```\n\n### The Minimal Fix Needed\n\nThe test needs to pass the `sql` instance to `createHealthRoutes`. In the test setup, you need to:\n\n1. The test file already has `rawSql` variable (line 98), which is the postgres instance\n2. Pass this `rawSql` as the `sql` parameter to `createHealthRoutes`:\n\n```typescript\ncreateHealthRoutes({\n  db,\n  sql: rawSql,  // ← Add this line\n  connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n  serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  isWorkerRunning: () => true,\n  minSolBalance: 0.1,\n});\n```\n\n**Root cause**: The spec 300 referral system added event queue monitoring to the health endpoint, which requires a direct SQL connection. The test was not updated to pass this new required parameter."}],"totalDurationMs":65888,"totalTokens":49992,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":659,"cache_read_input_tokens":48465,"output_tokens":868,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":659},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
